        self.payment_processor = payment_processor

    def process(self, amount):
        self.payment_processor.process_payment(amount)
```
**ISP and LSP are not applicable in this case as there is no inheritance or polymorphism involved.** 

The code provided does not violate ISP (Interface Segregation Principle) nor LSP (Liskov Substitution Principle). These principles apply when we have multiple interfaces and classes that implement these interfaces, but in this case there is only one class implementing an interface. The high-level module `PaymentProcessor` does not depend on details of low-level modules like `FreePaymentProcessor`; it uses abstractions (interfaces).

